    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">How much does the Tromsø University Museum cost?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Adults pay €11.00 (130 NOK). Children under 18 and UiT university students enter free. Senior citizens 67+, people with disabilities, students, and military conscripts pay €8.50 (100 NOK). Groups of 10 or more pay €8.50 per person. An annual pass costs €43.00 (500 NOK) and covers the passholder plus one guest. See en.uit.no/tmu/planlegg for current prices.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">What are the opening hours?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Winter season (16 Aug–14 Jun): Mon–Fri 10:00–16:30, Sat–Sun 11:00–16:00. Summer season (15 Jun–15 Aug): Mon–Fri 10:00–18:00, Sat–Sun 11:00–17:00. Closed 1 January, 1 May, 17 May, 24 December, and 25 December.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">How do I get to the University Museum?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The museum is at Lars Thørings veg 10, 2.5 km south of the city centre. Bus number 40 from the city centre stops at Tromsø Museum. By car, guest parking with accessible spaces is available on site; fees paid via Easypark app or the nearby ticket machine. On foot or by bike, the popular Telegrafbukta beach is 300 m away and a cycle path connects from Kvaløyvegen.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Are guided tours available in English?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Yes. Two English-language guided tours run weekly: "Discover the Aurora" every Tuesday at 14:00, and "Sami Culture — Past and Present" every Thursday at 14:00, during fall 2025 and spring 2026 seasons (with exceptions for national holidays). Advance booking recommended at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="54363b3b3f3d3a33142039217a213d207a3a3b">[email&#160;protected]</a> or through the museum's online calendar at en.uit.no/tmu.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Is there food and parking at the museum?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Café Rotunden is on site, serving coffee, tea, soft drinks and snacks during opening hours. On Sundays it operates with staff from 12:00–15:30 serving waffles. Paid guest car parking is directly adjacent to the building entrance; two accessible spaces are available. The museum shop is open during museum hours and accessible without a ticket.</div>
    </div>
